    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and finely chop them, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Zest<strong> </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>chicken mince</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley & mint </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands are the best way!)</p><p>Divide and shape into meatballs (5 per person!) \u2013 these are your <strong>herby meatballs</strong></p><p>Tip: Use wet hands to make it easier!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until lightly browned</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Once browned, set aside on a plate, reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>orzo</strong>, 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and the <strong>browned meatballs</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the orzo is tender and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is tender and the meatballs are cooked, add the your <strong>soft cheese </strong>with the <strong>wilted spinach</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>one pan</strong> <strong>herby meatballs with creamy lemon orzo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-meatballs-with-creamy-lemon-orzo-and-tenderstem-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the <strong>one pan</strong> <strong>herby meatballs with creamy lemon orzo</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong>, the <strong>remaining chopped parsley & mint</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
